<TITLE> 121 firearms missing 2 months after mutiny </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 21 (bdnews24.com)Some 121 firearms are still missing from Bangladesh Rifles Peelkhana headquarters two months after the Feb 25-26 mutiny, BDR authorities said on Tuesday. A statement by the border force said police, with the help of army personnel, had completed the tally and identification of BDR weapons recovered after the mutiny. It said 121 firearms of different models were unaccounted for. Some weapons were broken and some had missing parts, it added. The missing weapons included 83 pistols, 17 rifles, four sub machine guns, two Walther PPK revolvers used by officers, seven other handguns, three rifles, two 12-bore shotguns and two single-barrelled shotguns. The rebellious border guards involved in the February uprising are said to have armed themselves by breaking into and looting the BDR armoury. In the aftermath of the mutiny, that left at least 70 dead, mostly army officers deputed to the boder force, RAB and police recovered weapons and ammunition lying scattered around the sprawling Peelkhana complex in Dhaka and from other parts of the country. bd
